    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Trailer Work or
        Hook-Up
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Trailer Work or Hook-Up</title>
        <table id="t0828017" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Trailer Work or Hook-Up</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.53in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.76in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.73in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.47in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At 10A fuse F1-D and circuit 14AN, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>F1-D, 14AN to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14K or 14AN from (B1) battery stud, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (25) and at circuit 65, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(25), 65 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in 10A fuse F1-D or cir. 65, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With work light switch (25) in off position, measure resistance from terminal 4 to
                                5.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Sw. (25), term. 4 to 5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Move work light switch (25) to on position and measure resistance from terminal 5 to
                                6.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Sw. (25), term. 5 to 6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect trailer work light conn. (N/L), and reconnect work light switch (25). At
                                conn. (N/L) and black wire, measure voltage to ground with switch (25) in the on
                                position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(N/L) black wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 65A or black wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With switch still set, at connector (N/L), measure voltage from black wire to circuit
                                11.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(N/L), black wire to 11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 11 to (J7) cab ground, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect trailer work light conn. (N/L). Does work light illuminate?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Repair or replace defective work light lamp or socket.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Does work light indicator illuminate?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to Step 12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect left gauge cluster connector (73), and with work light switch in on
                                position, measure voltage from circuit 65B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(73), 65B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 65B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With switch still set, at connector (73), measure voltage from circuit 65B to 11-GV.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(73), 65B to 11-GV.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in cir. 11-GV or 11-GF to left cab ground stud (429),
                                then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect left gauge cluster connector (73). Does work light indicator light
                                illuminate?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective bulb or socket assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Trailer work light circuits check good. Move work light switch to off position.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
